<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"The_Kabsch_algorithm">The K=
absch algorithm</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editse=
ction-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?titl=
e=3DSingular_value_decomposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D20" title=
=3D"Edit section: The Kabsch algorithm"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D=
"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kabsch_algorithm" title=3D"=
Kabsch algorithm">Kabsch algorithm</a> (called <a href=3D"https://en.wikipe=
dia.org/wiki/Wahba%27s_problem" title=3D"Wahba's problem">Wahba's problem</=
a> in other fields) uses SVD to compute the optimal rotation (with respect =
to least-squares minimization) that will align a set of points with a corre=
sponding set of points. It is used, among other applications, to compare th=
e structures of molecules.
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Principal_Component_Analysi=
s">Principal Component Analysis</h3><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span cl=
ass=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/=
w/index.php?title=3DSingular_value_decomposition&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;sect=
ion=3D21" title=3D"Edit section: Principal Component Analysis"><span>edit</=
span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></div>
<p>The SVD can be used to construct the principal components in <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Principal_component_analysis" title=3D"Princi=
