-align: -0.338ex; width:1.764ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle R}"=
></span> matrix. The elementary iteration zeroes a pair of off-diagonal ele=
ments by first applying a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Givens_r=
otation" title=3D"Givens rotation">Givens rotation</a> to symmetrize the pa=
ir of elements and then applying a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki=
/Jacobi_transformation" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Jacobi transformatio=
n">Jacobi transformation</a> to zero them,
<span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-block"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-display mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math di=
